goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of fertility vs life expectancy
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a relationship between fertility and life expectancy. If there is a negative correlation, it could indicate that countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility rates across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of fertility rates across countries. It could indicate if there are any outliers or if the majority of countries have similar fertility rates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancies across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of life expectancies across countries. It could indicate if there are any outliers or if the majority of countries have similar life expectancies.

goals.question: How do the fertility rates of developed countries compare to those of developing countries?
goals.visualization: box plot of fertility rates by country classification
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a significant difference in fertility rates between developed and developing countries. It could indicate if there are any trends or patterns in fertility rates based on a country's level of development.

goals.question: How do the life expectancies of developed countries compare to those of developing countries?
goals.visualization: box plot of life expectancies by country classification
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a significant difference in life expectancies between developed and developing countries. It could indicate if there are any trends or patterns in life expectancies based on a country's level of development.

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility', 'life_expect']]
    sns.scatterplot(x='fertility', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility']]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['fertility'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rates across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility', 'country_classification']]
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="country_classification", y="fertility", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Country Classification', ylabel='Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('How do the fertility rates of developed countries compare to those of developing countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['life_expect', 'country_classification'])
    data['country_classification'] = data['country_classification'].astype('category')
    data['life_expect'] = data['life_expect'].astype('float')
    sns.boxplot(x='country_classification', y='life_expect', data=data, palette='Set3')
    plt.title('How do the life expectancies of developed countries compare to those of developing countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country Classification')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
